<paragraph id="B4A42EDD7C3BD317732C2A4347A4C9EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnose.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2DEE991BEB2817BC709493DE40EDAB93" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="13C39708428A0D86E78A3C887FAFC253" authorityName="Padua &amp; Saeaeksjaervi" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polysphincta macroepomia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroepomia">
<emphasis id="F03C28AFF9BBE40B4C81C68487701943" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Polysphincta macroepomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="C90C74E7C265DD66A91B03D41EFAEEE1" genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis id="75CE7F37F249D82F1C9F243A4CB78DBF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the combination of the following characters: (1) epomia present, 1.5 times length of proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="109557D985E05E2A3C5D090900A5BB06" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5B</figureCitation>
); (2) malar space 0.6 times as long as proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6F0041CDC21349EB92E88D542A7DA005" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5B</figureCitation>
); (3) fore wing vein 1 
<emphasis id="1C0D2843210E73652B0DCEA07BD2B150" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">cu-a</emphasis>
interstitial relative to 
<emphasis id="85AEDEE87BB6F4BA125EC2BCBDC9FE70" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9939B7C73A32AB9B5333024730F290CD" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5A</figureCitation>
); (4) mesosoma orange, except metapleuron and propodeum darkish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B589B6E3F381CB0AFEC4E8734E13AC86" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5A</figureCitation>
); (5) fore wing hyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="498879AD6B55C3276AA7C70DAE34E2C7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5A</figureCitation>
); (6) hind leg whitish with spot in proximal region of coxa, base of trochanter, longitudinal spot in subdistal region of inner and outer margin of femur, distal part of tibia and distal part of tarsus brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="218514686F3C9FC345EE38815A1A36E9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5A</figureCitation>
); (7) metasoma darkish brown, with posterior margins of tergites II-V narrowly black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ABB590EA6472A99394A156D1D5B4B6ED" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Polysphincta macroepomia sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550746" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">5A, C</figureCitation>
); (8) ovipositor slightly slender, 1.7 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
