<paragraph id="41754374581A2DD19585917EAEA25F57" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="100C86542E6B81AE52252AD1E07DC348" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="3A11383EAF5157555E9B820248F8EE04" authorityName="Padua &amp; Saeaeksjaervi" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polysphincta macroepomia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroepomia">
<emphasis id="E9B5EA11A41BFBCF78960D3E622BD142" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Polysphincta macroepomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="FE033D20A750EA3CF99CD8DE19ED7D5D" genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis id="390190803E90334453B34A13244D6222" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gauld, 1991 and 
<taxonomicName id="2D56096218F84F88422A035ED0B2A66E" genus="P." lsidName="P. cosnipata" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="cosnipata">
<emphasis id="3D45CA5FC8623E9A68F2734BC614F5FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. cosnipata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. mainly by the coloration, mesosoma orange with metapleuron and propodeum blackish and metasoma brownish or blackish. However, it differs from both species by having epomia present (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="D264EB0DF524073F5BA734C10C505F47" genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis id="B7418EF87D5BA4549A0D71F315ED3857" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0D82A4B6497242D34E660ADB33B7BF52" genus="P." lsidName="P. cosnipata" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="cosnipata">
<emphasis id="72E08FC074CC7A9F8EE127E5E1A78AB2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. cosnipata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.).
</paragraph>
